@kghosesbg  My plan was first to write the pysam objects in each subprocess to a buffer and if the buffer is full to write all elements of this buffer out to a BAM file, but this step should be done by the main process to prevent multiple access to the output which is a slowdown. As mentioned above this is not working. To overcome this limitation I write now in each process a BAM file to /dev/shm (aka my 'buffer') and run an additional process which is merging the BAM files (close the BAM file if the 'buffer' is full) into one big BAM file. 
I do not really communicate with the BAM files between the processes, I just write the result of each process out to a bam file. After this is done I have multiple BAM files and I merge them. If you are interested in the real implementation have a look: https://github.com/joachimwolff/HiCExplorer/blob/profile_performance/hicexplorer/hicBuildMatrix.py. 
Of interest is: Line 914, 915, function 'write_bam', line 925 which is running with a background process.

